Media notes: Mexican Jay, adult attacking corpse of 2nd Mexican Jay, Cave Creek Canyon, Coronado National Forest, Cochise County AZ, 24 Sept 2020, Carol R. Comeau
Observation Details: The adult Mexican Jay was undeterred by my presence. The attack continued during the entire 15  minute observation period. The bird constantly stabbed at the dead jay. It would come up with mouthfuls of feathers. I never saw any meat.  It was still attacking when I left. There were 2-3 other Mexican Jays in the area calling.  When I returned approximately 2 hours later, the attacking jay was gone. I was able to examine the dead Mexican Jay. It was a banded adult. I submitted a banding report. For a Youtube video on the attack, select the picture: <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Ef-s8lYQnlA" frameborder="0"></iframe>

Large jays with solid deep blue uppers, pale below, and distinctive call. The group flew back and forth across the hillside multiple times. A bit surprised to see them this low in elevation. Recordings and bad photos obtained.
